Chippa United were held to a goalless draw by Bloemfontein Celtic in the Absa Premiership at Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium on Tuesday night.Celtic almost took the lead in the 33rd minute but Fiston Abdoul s shot was saved by Chippa goalkeeper. The visitors created clear chances in the second half more than Chippa but Celtic failed to bury their chances. Just after the start of the second stanza, former Orlando player Menzi Masuku s tried to score from outside the box but his shot went over the crossbar. In the closing stages, Chippa nearly snatched a win when Thembinkosi Lorch fired a shot at goal, but his strike hit the woodwork as the game ended 0-0.